# External GLB model location
# Option A: Direct URL (S3/R2/Blob/CDN). Must allow CORS: Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
# Example:
# VITE_MODEL_URL=https://your-cdn.example.com/models/ttu-0911-1000000-r00.glb
#
# Option B: Google Drive
# Paste the public sharing link OR just the file ID. Prefer Drive API for stable CORS.
# Example share link:
#   https://drive.google.com/file/d/FILE_ID/view?usp=sharing
# Set either:
#  - VITE_MODEL_URL with the share link (we'll parse FILE_ID), OR
#  - VITE_GDRIVE_FILE_ID with the id only
# Optional (recommended): Drive API key for CORS-safe download:
#   VITE_GDRIVE_API_KEY=your-api-key
#
# The app resolves final URL as:
#   If VITE_GDRIVE_FILE_ID and VITE_GDRIVE_API_KEY set:
#     https://www.googleapis.com/drive/v3/files/{FILE_ID}?alt=media&key={API_KEY}
#   Else if only FILE_ID/share link set:
#     https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id={FILE_ID}
#   Else: uses VITE_MODEL_URL as-is (or falls back to local /ttu-0911-1000000-r00.glb)

# Example with your current file:
# Share link: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1G0v29RN0Jjqkk-mwlfYYSaFmjhMMXROz/view?usp=sharing
VITE_GDRIVE_FILE_ID=1G0v29RN0Jjqkk-mwlfYYSaFmjhMMXROz
# VITE_GDRIVE_API_KEY=YOUR_GOOGLE_API_KEY
# VITE_MODEL_URL= # leave empty when using Drive above